devdoc.title: The Alyra Final Project which is named the WineNotBlockhain Marketplace

addCollateral(uint256).notice: The producer has to add a Collateral when the owner of one of his bottles would like to receive the bottle. It is a safety measure to protect the buyer.

buyBottle(uint256).notice: Buy a Bottle that is for sales

confirmDelivery(uint256).notice: The owner of a WineBottle confirms that he has received the Bottle at his home. It will release the collateral

contestShipment(uint256).notice: The owner of a WineBottle can contest the Shipment if he did not receive the Bottle. WineNotBlockchain will handle the issue with the producer. Once the issue is solved, the owner can confirm the delivery.

getBottleOwner(uint256).notice: Return the Owner of a Bottle

getBottleSaleInfo(uint256).notice: Return the current sale status of a Bottle

getBottleStatus(uint256).notice: Return the Status of the Bottle

getBottleURI(uint256).notice: Return info about a Bottle Image

getBottlesBalance().notice: Return the number of NFT owned by the sender

getCollateralInfo(uint256).notice: Return all the Sales of a Bottle

getSalesHistory(uint256).notice: Return all the Sales of a Bottle

getTotalSupply().notice: Return the number of NFT created

indicateShipmentToProducer(uint256).notice: The owner of a WineBottle would like to drink or receive his bottle and he indicates the producer to ship his bottle We suppose that there is a way to communicate with the producer through a dedicated message app (to send him his shipping address for example)

isCallerOwner().notice: Return true if the Owner called the function

isWhitelistedProducer(address).notice: Check if a producer is whitelisted

mintWineBottle(string,string,uint256,uin.notice: A producer can mint a Bottle

revokeProducer(address).notice: Delete a producer from the whitelist
